e described her as being very "pale" and state that she doesn't move during these events. She then has severe events that she descibes as being "convulsions" characterized by "back spasms" with shaking of her arms and spasms of her neck. She feels like she isn't herself during these events, but doesn't believe that she completely loses consciousness. She states that she occasionally doesn't remember these events. They usually last approximately one to two and a half minutes each and usually feels confused afterwards. They occur approximately once a month, with the last one occurring a six days ago. She has been seen at ___, where it was thought that these episodes were either non-epileptogenic in na

